data.title: Duke University
data.meta_description: We at Duke University engineer therapeutic materials to promote wound healing and tissue regeneration (think Wolverine without the blades).
data.text: We engineer therapeutic materials to promote wound healing and tissue regeneration (think Wolverine without the blades). Our methods involve chemically modifying polymers that mimic tissue structure, then applying our material to wound beds to study their effects. We get fancy and incorporate additional factors, like genes and drugs, and have also created a new class of granular material called M.A.P. that’s been trending since 2015. We’ve tested our material in brain, skin, and bone defects, and the exciting results drive us to continue exploring. Our mission is shared by members of the scientific, medical, and patient community, and we have massive love for everyone involved in the collaborative effort.
